reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars IT REALLY WORKS
reviews.reviewText: I don’t know what kind of sorcery they put in here, but it works and it works fast. Have a smell that’s bugging you? Sensitive to scents and don’t want to add another one to it? This is the stuff you’re looking for. Fragrance free (and actually, it doesn’t smell like anything), put this thing out and that smell is gone.I do wish it was environmentally friendlier, because they only last a few weeks and it’s a lot of packaging to have to keep replacing. It would be nice if they had refills or something. It’s also not very cute. But for temporary utilitarian purposes, it does the job and it does it well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Seems to work!
reviews.reviewText: I was pleasantly surprised. I have a closet that just always had a smell, never figured out why. Put one of these in the closet and that smell has dissipated. So awesome to be able to open the door and not instantly scrunch up my nose. Any other freshener - beads, gels - anything with a scent would just compound the problem. This No Scent charcoal odor eliminator has really worked. It's been almost 30 days and the smell has yet to return. Will be buying more for other areas of the house.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I put it in my room and it works very well!Great deal as it is much cheaper than other brands.Just be careful when taking off the inner seal because the gel can get on your have if your not careful.Also, if your looking for these as a fragrance, this product is not a good idea. The charcoal only removes the smell, not puts out perfume.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I needed this for under our kitchen sink cabinet. I was amazed at how quickly it worked within 30 minutes of placing under our sink, the smell was instantly gone. Unfortunately it only worked for about a week and a half and the product says works up to 30 days.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Removed the stench of death from a decomposing body. Highly recommended
reviews.reviewText: I had a big problem that I needed to take care of. I got into my car one morning and I was hit with the stench of death. I believe a mouse or other rodent got into my engine and met his or her untimely demise. Unfortunately for me, the mouse decided to leave a lasting impression.I tried many things first. I tried a container of white vinegar and baking soda several times (seemed to help but did not last. Then I used half a bottle of Fabreze over the course of a week. That sort of helped, but I still smelled my friend's decomposition.Then I found this item! I typically don't write reviews for everyday items, but I had to write this. The product is excellent. Within a few hours, the small really got knocked down. And then with about a day, I could no longer smell the dead body that had been haunting me for weeks.I highly recommend this product, particularly if you have a smell you want to get rid of, decomposing body or otherwise.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My mother loves fried stuff but I can't stand the smell especially after she cooks fried fish. I put this odor eliminator in the kitchen and I stuck around. At first I thought it didn't work because the smell was still there. After a couple of minutes, I thought, ok it works just a little because the smell is not as evident. I left the kitchen for a few minutes and returned and realize the smell that used to linger for hours is now gone! I'm definitely going to make this a routine household item!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Scent is very mild
reviews.reviewText: The product scent is very mild. Using it in a room with no windows (10’x12’) with one ceiling vent - poor circulation. The product does little to help the stuffy/staleness of the room. I was hoping it would do more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Clothes to but not perfect
reviews.reviewText: My young adult son showers religiously & doesn’t smell as a whole, but when I walked into his room it would be like being punched in the face with a perfume of an old man smothered in blue cheese dressing. This was probably caused by his dirty clothes filled with young man hormonal sweat being piled with his damp towels. Placed this little baby next to his pile & almost all of the stench has disappeared. I’m very happy with the purchase even if it wasn’t perfect.
